title: palm beach to philadelphia
text: American is a solid airline. The last flight was delayed some 20 minutes and they told me why which I appreciated. The best thing, we landed on time anyway. The service for drinks was well organized. We were comfortable and the plane was clean. We fly American all the time to Florida but we always pay for better seats.

title: Cheerful dinner in Boca
text: Last night was an excellent meal. I had the filet mignon and it was cooked to perfection. There is usually a choice to eat outside or inside. The outside bar had a reservation for a large party but we sat by the window. It is worth your time.

title: Real Mexican restaurant
text: We went to the Mariachi Grill after reading all the reviews in the area and we were not disappointed t all. The waitress was engaging and knew the menu well. I liked my food and so did my wife. It was clean and a nice atmosphere.
place: Mexican Mariachi Grill y Tequila Bar

title: DUBLIN TO PHILADELPHIA was first class
text: I thought the service was very good and so did my wife and we fly often. The seats turn into a bed and we were offered champagne or wine of our choice. The food was good, check-in was smooth and I would fly with them again.

title: The best of Glassboro
text: There are not a lot of places I can say I never had a bad meal if I went there many times but I can say that about the Monarch Diner. The owners and managers are very alert to what is going on at the busy times in the diner. The service is top shelve and the food is fresh. If there is one complaint it would be the parking. There are times there is such a rush and I may need to park across the street. Nice problem to have if you are a restaurant.

title: EXPERIENCE MODERN JAPANESE
text: We had a group of 8 and it was a wonderful time for everyone. Our waiter explained the menu and the choices. He was excellent. We all got the $75.00 per person and ate just about everything the restaurant had to offer. The steak was perfect and I had this drink called Widow of The East and was really good. The atmosphere was good but a little too dark so bring your flashlight. This is high end dinning but worth the experience.

title: A well organized diner
text: I previously spoke about Monarch's breakfast and have been back several times, never to be disappointed. If you go on a Sunday morning you will see a big crowd, but do not let that deflate you. This is a well organized restaurant that moves people in & out like clock-work. I went to lunch recently and it was very good.

title: Best seat in the house
text: This is a remarkable view for a restaurant. The food is very good. a variety of drinks but you may need to wait a bit because it gets very packed.

title: New Jersey to Athens
text: It was so exciting to see something so ancient. The caretakers have done an excellent job of preserving this Greek culture from many years ago. It is worth your time.

title: Best view of Athens
text: Hey you want to see the most beautiful view of the Acropolis and the Parthenon at night time you will want to go to the 11th floor at this hotel. Sit outside in the nice Greek atmosphere and watch the sunset on a lighted Acropolis while you sip your favorite wine. The food is good and bathrooms are small but you will forget all that when you sit outside on the top floor looking at the brilliantly glowing ancient Acropolis. I recommend the Titania.

title: The Titanic comes alive.
text: There are many facts about the Titanic that are all brought to light in this comprehensive exhibition. Everyone in our group enjoyed the visit and guides were very pleasant.
place: Titanic Belfast Entrance Ticket: Titanic Visitor Experience Including SS Nomadic

title: Bond, James Bond. That Casino.
text: It is just part of Monte Carlo and legend. The elegant casino is good for a short visit unless you are a gambler but when you walk out, look around to see some of the most expensive autos in one place you may ever see. We did not eat there so I can not comment but rumor has it, It is very good.

title: King crab & raw clams are the best
text: Seafood and bring your own salad because this is a special restaurant. The new owner copied exactly the previous owner's everything. My opinion is it is the best raw claws anywhere. The large king crab is something you need to experience. Some evenings there is a piano player and the d√©cor
place: Joseph's Original Cap'n Cat Clam Bar

title: Best of Washington Twp.
text: This restaurant has been around since the 70s but has never been better managed since Otts has made it a complete bar & restaurant. Outside dinning or belly up to two large bars you get a good choice of bar type food. Some nights there are good live bands playing.

title: Best breakfast in town.
text: Oldies but goodies is the 1950s atmosphere. I have been here many times and never had a bad breakfast. Fresh made orange juice made right in front of you. My favorite is chip cream beef egg omlett . Great service

title: Fine Italian Cucina.
text: If your looking for the best Italian fine dinning in South Jersey you need to go to Scarpinatos restaurant. I can tell you besides great food it is real hard not to bring a portion home with you. The new place is large & Elegant. The meatball balls are outstanding as well as the spinach egg drop soup.

title: Best breakfast around.
text:
This is a place you will know the whole menu is very good. The Monarch Diner is a family restaurant under new management. Many Greek style dishes and it is delicious. Try Diablo Omlete if you like hot & spicey.

guarantee you will not leave hungry

title: Asian food you will enjoy
text: I have been to this restaurant many times and always had a good experience. China, Japan type food which has many various choices. IT is good food and good prices,

title: Back in time Diner.
text: If you like that old time diner atmosphere with good food and even better prices, you may need to wait a bit but Angelo's is the place. Eat at the counter or the small booths and enjoy your breakfast, lunch or dinner. Just cash like old school but you will smile when you see your check.

title: FEAST on the Delaware
text: If you like eating outside looking over the Delaware River and the Riverwinds golf course nearby you will enjoy this pleasant restaurant. The drinks & food are good. It is managed well and you can sit inside looking over the lively river.

title: Sports bar in the college
text: Chickie's & Pete's is the same or not better than the ones in Philadelphia. If you like a sports atmosphere, college kids, and bar food, this is for you.

title: Bar food at its best
text: I gave the Landmark an excellent rating with the understanding it is essentially a bar restaurant that is clean and well managed. It is a large center bar but plenty of tables even for families in separate rooms.

title: The Basilica of old & modern art.
text: This structure is unique like no other in all of history. It started construction in 1883 and it is still not completed. It is an extraordinary interpretation of Gothic architecture. The tour lines move in an organized manner, so do not let the crowds bother you. If you are in Barcelona, this is a must see.

title: PHILADELPHIA TO EUROPE
text: I was so thankful we paid extra for the PREMIUM ECONOMY SEATS. Plenty of room and the FOOD was very GOOD. The flight ATTENDANTS were really pleasant. AMERICAN AIRLINES is among the better AIRLINES.

title: Atlantic Ave Fine restaurant.
text: We have eaten here many times and the food is very good. I do not believe you can get any better food for this price in Delray Beach.

title: Relax by the water.
text: We have been to deck 84 many times. Anyone who visits us in Delray Beach we take to this restaurant and everyone enjoys themselves. Good food, good music and just a great view of the boats coming and going. The service is always top shelve.

title: One of the best in Delray Beach.
text: It looks like a bar/restaurant in New York city and if your looking for fine dinning and great food, this is the place. Very good seafood menu and worth the trip.

title: Prado Museum
text: This museum is outstanding in every respect. Some of the best painters ever has their work of art displayed at the Prado Museum. It is a must see
place: Go Madrid Explorer Pass including Prado Museum and Real Madrid Tour

title: Spain to New Jersey
text: This church is different than any Church or Basilica you will ever see. Fantastic work of art. It is a must see when in Barcelona.
place: Basilica of the Sagrada Familia Admission Ticket

title: Spain to New Jersey
text: Excellent hotel. Service was very good. The entire Hotel is clean. Security is very good also. The location of the hotel is convenient in seeing the whole city.The price is fair for all you are offered.
